column2: So far, we have served over 100,000 meals to frontliners and communities in need through our Kindness Kitchens. This wouldn't have been possible without your do...nations. We are thankful for the support of our volunteers and partners, ABS-CBN, Coca-Cola, Angkas, Remington, Ecolab, TBWA, OMD, Leo Burnett, Seven A.D., PayMaya, Shopee, Isla, Liquigaz, Petron, Philam Foundation, Share Treats, M2Cash Corporation, and HAVI. Thank you for helping us serve kindness in these trying times. You may still donate at rmhc.org.ph/donate to help us continue to serve kindness.

Train like a Spartan even at home! Join the daily virtual workouts of our Spartan Ambassadors -- live on Instagram! Check out the schedule below. Live a healthier, longer, better life with #PhilamVitality! Visit this link to find out more: http://bit.ly/PLVitality

We have partnered with Bayanihan Musikahan and Puhon: Ben&Ben to deliver PPES, test kits and transportation to those who need it the most. We are also supporting food security programs for those who have lost their capacity to earn. In doing so, we feel that we are able to fulfill our mission of helping Filipinos race against risk to live a healthier, longer, better life. We invite you to participate and give what you can to those who need it the most. Let us all do what we can to #FlattenTheCurve!

column2: #UPDATE as of March 17: With the implementation of the enhanced community quarantine by the Philippine Government, AIA Philam Life has temporarily suspended the operations of our hotline and customer service centers in Luzon until April 12, 2020. Here are branches outside of the quarantine that remain open from Monday to Friday, 10am to 3pm: Cebu, Iloilo*, Ozamis, Cagayan de Oro, General Santos, and Davao*. We remain committed to assisting you on your policy-related needs during these trying times. CLICK on the images below to learn more how we can help you in the coming weeks. IMPORTANT NOTE: *As of March 20, our Ilo-ilo and Davao branches have also temporarily suspended operations.

In AXA, we are committed to promoting women empowerment in the workplace, with programs that help advance their health and wellbeing and those that support the needs of working mothers. In celebration of Women‚Äôs Month, we give back to the women in the communities in which we work with a free cervical screening activity for public school teachers in partnership with the Philippine Cancer Society, and a financial literacy session to benefit the female employees of DepEd Manila.... We also put the spotlight on some of the remarkable WoMen@AXA through an exhibit that recognizes their strength of character, dedication to their profession, and their passion and purpose.  In photo: Peachy and Zaida are exemplary examples of women of strength, character and integrity. Peachy is married, a mother of three and a breast cancer survivor. Zaida is a single, independent woman that loves her furbabies. Peachy is a training and development professional, and Zaida is a certified internal auditor. Both of them excel in their chosen fields and lead fulfilling lives with work-life harmony.

The Insular Foundation, one of the first corporate foundations in the Philippines, has raised over P2M for our healthcare workers in the past 2 days through InLife employees, financial advisors, policyholders, and their close family & friends. Now, we are calling on the public for donations to purchase in bulk Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) for healthcare providers and first responders dealing with those impacted by the pandemic. Any amount you give will be matched 1:1, ...peso-for-peso, by the Foundation. You may send your donations through: ‚Ä¢ BPI - Account Name: Insular Foundation, Account No: 8841-0005-61 ‚Ä¢ Paypal - paypal.me/InsularFoundation and e-mail a screenshot of your confirmed transaction to info.foundation@insular.com.ph for an Official Receipt to be issued. Check your InLife policy if you have the I-Heal plan, a Lazada Premium Protect plan, or any individual life insurance plan with a hospitalization benefit (rider) attached to it. We want to help you focus on your recovery and relieve your loved ones of any more worry.

column2: Advisory: Here's how we are processing your investment transactions after the reopening of the equities and fixed income markets.

column2: With the growing concern about COVID-19 and FWD's continuing commitment to care for customers, FWD is providing existing plan holders ‚ÄúFWD COVID-19 Ready,‚Äù an additional lump sum medical and funeral benefit if diagnosed with COVID-19, at no extra cost. This benefit is provided on top of eligible and active FWD insurance plans and riders. In addition, for customers who are diagnosed with COVID-19, FWD will be extending payment grace period to 90 days and releasing the FWD COVI...D-19 Ready medical benefit claims within 48 hours. All other policies will have an extended payment grace period of 60 days. Ask your financial advisor for details or contact our 24/7 LiveChat at fwd.com.ph and on our mobile app, FWD Tapp. Learn more at bit.ly/FWDCOVID19Ready Benefit is available for active and eligible life insurance plans issued up to Feb 29, 2020, except group insurance plans, KanDuu (KanMend, KanLive, and KanGuard), Set Ka Na, and Peace. Special coverage period is from March 9 to April 15. #FWDCOVID19Ready

column2: With the growing concern about COVID-19 and FWD's continuing commitment to care for customers, FWD is providing existing plan holders ‚ÄúFWD COVID-19 Ready,‚Äù  an additional lump sum medical and funeral benefit if diagnosed with COVID-19, at no extra cost. This benefit is provided on top of eligible and active FWD insurance plans and riders. In addition, for customers who are diagnosed with COVID-19, FWD will be extending payment grace period to 90 days and releasing the FWD COV...ID-19 Ready medical benefit claims within 48 hours. Ask your financial advisor for details or contact our 24/7 LiveChat at fwd.com.ph and on our mobile app, FWD Tapp. Learn more at bit.ly/FWDCOVID19Ready Benefit is available for active and eligible life insurance plans issued up to Feb 29, 2020, except group insurance plans, KanDuu (KanMend, KanLive, and KanGuard), Set Ka Na, and Peace. Coverage period until April 15. #FWDCOVID19Ready

column2: At FWD, our vision is to change the way people feel about insurance. We listen to you and work tirelessly to redefine insurance through your eyes.  When we assist you, we go above and beyond to put ourselves in your shoes first.  We want to give you the protection you need through easy-to-understand products, supported by digital technology. We focus on your other needs as much as your financial ones. We continue to innovate to provide you the best service‚Äîquick, easy, and hassle-free.    We‚Äôre here for you when you need us. We became the first insurance company in the Philippines to offer 24/7 customer service and launched Tapp, our one-tap insurance app, that allows you to manage your plans at the touch of your fingers. We want you to celebrate living without fear because we always have your back.

Driving in the Philippines means you‚Äôll spend countless hours stuck in heavy traffic. It‚Äôs the reality. With this, always assume that most people are in a sour mood already and their patience is wearing thin by the minute. Refrain from doing anything aggressive that will only add fuel to the fire. Maintain the proper speed and observe adequate space for lane changes. If a motorist is tailgating you, move over and let them go. Remember: It isn‚Äôt worth causing an accident or serious injury, just to prove you‚Äôre right. If you expect disciplined driving from others, start with yourself. #FWDMCX #RoadToProgress #GetReadyToLive

column2: If you‚Äôre trying to stick to a budget, it‚Äôs better to shop without the direct or indirect influence (aka peer pressure) from others. The ‚Äúdangers‚Äù are obvious: buying something you don‚Äôt like or won‚Äôt use or can‚Äôt afford just because someone said it was nice on you. Just think of the things you‚Äôre actually saving and how sticking to your budget will get you closer to getting that.  #GetReadyToLive #FWDFinancialSelfCareTip

Breast cancer may not be preventable, but it has a high survival rate and surgeries (like a lumpectomy and mastectomy) are viable options for treatment. A breast cancer diagnosis is life-changing, but the right mindset backed by the proper financial protection can definitely help you in your fight. #GetRadyToLive #FWDPlanWithPurpose

column2: Your vehicle‚Äôs horn should only be used when necessary and not just because you want to make noise and express annoyance to another motorist. If you can help it, don‚Äôt show displeasure to other drivers, minimizing the risk of getting into an altercation or road rage accident. No matter how many times you press your horn, it will not make traffic go faster, so best to have your hands useful on the wheel or gear stick. Listen to music or even meditate to calm yourself. #FWDMCX #RoadToProgress #GetReadyToLive

FWD Philippines, part of pan-Asian insurer FWD Group, supported DIWATA Women in Resource Development Inc.'s "2020 Sulong Program" -- a gathering of partners and stakeholders of the Tanging Tanglaw Project -- today at Sitio Caguing in Bamban, Tarlac.  In 2018 and 2019, FWD -- in collaboration with BAYAN Academy -- delivered a Financial Sustainability Training under the Tanging Tanglaw project, that taught the importance of financial literacy as well as opened livelihood opportunities to the Aeta community of Bamban, Tarlac. #FWDCommunityCare #GetReadyToLive In photo: FWD Philippines Board Member Atty. Leo Dominguez (second from left) with FWD volunteers led by Vice President & Head of Marketing Roche Vandenberghe (fourth from left).

column2: Due to local government guidelines to manage the COVID-19 health emergency across the country, our business centers in Iloilo and Tacloban are temporarily close...d until further notice. In addition, our Davao business centers will also cease operations effective Thursday, March 26. Offices in Luzon will remain closed. Our live customer service will not be available until further notice. Customers may reach out to their financial advisors for any concern on their policies. Alternatively, customers may review and manage their policies through customer portal PRUAccess at https://pruaccess.prulifeuk.com.ph/ or email PRU Customer Action Team at contact.us@prulifeuk.com.ph. We continue to assess and release more timely announcements as the local authorities implement further measures and guidelines.

column2: Happy #WorldHealthDay! We've been sharing workouts that you can do at home so you can keep yourself healthy and fit ‚Äî but remember that it is just as important to keep your mind in good shape. Practice mindfulness, give yourself the breaks that you deserve, give time to what you love, and do what aligns with your moral compass because these are the ways that you take care of your mental well-being. At the end of this pandemic and lockdown, make sure that you stay in agreement with yourself.

column2: Sun Life Foundation, in partnership with ECHOSI Foundation, started Project TALA (Tradition, Arts, and Livelihood Advocacy) to help preserve the inabal weaving tradition of the Bagobo-Tagabawa tribe in Bansalan, Davao del Sur through livelihood-building activities and skills training. In this initiative, the Bagobo-Tagabawa tribeswomen take the lead in planning, implementation, and management of community development initiatives, which in the past were the domain of men. #WomensMonth #BrighterWorldBuilders

column2: We are extending the grace period for premium payments to 91 days to make things a bit easier for our clients during this trying time. This extension is applicable for policies or pre-need plans with due dates falling from Feb. 15 to May 31, 2020. We will also start accepting soft copies of requirements related to any insurance claims. See our other advisories here: bit.ly/2w7FZlr #sunlifeadvisory
